Easier colormap construction

Phil Elson

data = np.linspace(-2, 4, 49).reshape(7, 7)
levels = [-1, 2, 2.5, 3]
colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'yellow', 'black']
extend = 'both'
cmap, norm = mcolors.from_levels_and_colors(levels, colors, extend=extend)

Housecleaning

Gone:

  • Qt (version 3)
  • Fltk
  • EMF (Enhanced Metafile)
  • nxutils
  • Printing support (was Wx-only)
  • pylab.save/pylab.load -- use numpy.savetxt and numpy.loadtxt instead.

Jae-Joon Lee

WebAgg backend

Michael Droettboom and Phil Elson

Other improvements

  • Colorbar extensions (Andrew Dawson)
  • Boxplot fixes (Paul Hobson)
  • Background color (Wes Campaigne and Phil Elson)
  • Improved tight bounding boxes
  • Text anchoring and alignment (Damon McDougall and Michael Droettboom)
  • Remember save directory (Marin Spacek)
  • New setup and configuration infrastructure
  • Bugs! Bugs! Bugs!
    • Phil Elson, Damon McDougall, Eric Firing and many others

MEPS

  • MEP8: Improve PEP8 compliance (Nelle Varoquaux)
  • MEP9: Interactive artists (Daniel Hyams)
  • MEP10: Modernize documentation (Nelle Varoquaux)
  • MEP12: Reorganize examples and gallery (Tony Yu)
  • MEP13: Use Python properties (Todd Jennings)
  • MEP14: Improve text handling (Michael Droettboom)

...join us at the matplotlib BOF for more discussion...
